00:05:18.818 --> 00:05:19.819 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Can we?

00:05:19.903 --> 00:05:21.071 position:50% align:center
s Of course.

00:05:21.154 --> 00:05:22.322 position:50% align:center
[HORIGUCHI] There aren't
many clouds out today,

00:05:22.405 --> 00:05:24.324 position:50% align:center
so you should have
a great view of the sky.

00:05:24.407 --> 00:05:25.742 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS gasp]

00:05:25.825 --> 00:05:28.328 position:50% align:center
We still have some of
last night's candy left, huh?

00:05:28.411 --> 00:05:29.621 position:50% align:center
Yep, a lot!

00:05:29.704 --> 00:05:31.247 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Let's bring drinks, too!

00:05:31.331 --> 00:05:32.457 position:50% align:center
[AO]
I need my camera.

00:05:36.753 --> 00:05:38.797 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS gasp]

00:05:41.007 --> 00:05:43.843 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Look at that! The Milky Way!

00:05:43.927 --> 00:05:46.971 position:50% align:center
[AO] It's my first time
seeing it this clearly.

00:05:47.055 --> 00:05:49.182 position:50% align:center
Oh, Mars is amazing!

00:05:49.265 --> 00:05:52.143 position:50% align:center
[MAKITA] Yeah, it's in
close approach this year, too.

00:05:52.227 --> 00:05:55.563 position:50% align:center
It's around negative two
or negative five right now.

00:05:55.647 --> 00:05:57.273 position:50% align:center
[TOMORI]
Hey, a shooting star!

00:05:57.357 --> 00:05:58.274 position:50% align:center
Ao, look!

00:05:58.358 --> 00:05:59.859 position:50% align:center
Yeah!

00:06:19.045 --> 00:06:20.422 position:50% align:center
Ah, I see.

00:06:20.505 --> 00:06:22.007 position:50% align:center
So, after this is over,
it's straight to

00:06:22.090 --> 00:06:23.967 position:50% align:center
entrance exams for you.

00:06:24.050 --> 00:06:26.219 position:50% align:center
I am taking them
this year so I can get started

00:06:26.302 --> 00:06:28.096 position:50% align:center
on summer courses.

00:06:28.179 --> 00:06:29.889 position:50% align:center
[TOMORI]
And what about you two?

00:06:29.973 --> 00:06:31.391 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:06:31.474 --> 00:06:33.935 position:50% align:center
[TOMORI] What will you do
after you discover an asteroid?

00:06:34.019 --> 00:06:35.854 position:50% align:center
[MAKITA] Do you think you might
try to become researchers

00:06:35.937 --> 00:06:37.480 position:50% align:center
like Hanashima?

00:06:39.816 --> 00:06:42.819 position:50% align:center
Our teacher asked us
the same thing once before.

00:06:42.902 --> 00:06:45.196 position:50% align:center
