while she's doing that.

00:11:19.512 --> 00:11:21.181 position:50% align:center
Sounds like a plan to me!

00:11:21.264 --> 00:11:23.016 position:50% align:center
Let's use pictures
of stars, too.

00:11:23.099 --> 00:11:24.934 position:50% align:center
That's a good idea.

00:11:25.018 --> 00:11:26.102 position:50% align:center
[HORIGUCHI, HANASHIMA]
Hmm.

00:11:32.067 --> 00:11:34.110 position:50% align:center
The summary pages
are all finished!

00:11:36.946 --> 00:11:40.241 position:50% align:center
Wow. Morning, already.

00:11:40.325 --> 00:11:42.077 position:50% align:center
All these memos and
photos you took throughout

00:11:42.160 --> 00:11:44.245 position:50% align:center
the process were
such a big help, Ao.

00:11:44.329 --> 00:11:45.663 position:50% align:center
Thank you so much!

00:11:45.747 --> 00:11:47.123 position:50% align:center
Oh, no.

00:11:47.207 --> 00:11:50.210 position:50% align:center
I felt bad for butting in
when I was just an observer.

00:11:50.293 --> 00:11:53.546 position:50% align:center
Although... I had
so much fun last night!

00:11:54.798 --> 00:11:57.217 position:50% align:center
[MAKITA] In that case,
maybe we can shift the subject

00:11:57.300 --> 00:11:59.552 position:50% align:center
and have a private convo
about your people skills.

00:11:59.636 --> 00:12:00.679 position:50% align:center
How about that?

00:12:00.762 --> 00:12:03.515 position:50% align:center
Only a few hours
until the presentation.

00:12:03.598 --> 00:12:04.974 position:50% align:center
[TOMORI]
Naptime.

00:12:09.312 --> 00:12:10.689 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
So, in the end,

00:12:10.772 --> 00:12:12.857 position:50% align:center
neither of the groups
were able to discover

00:12:12.941 --> 00:12:15.777 position:50% align:center
a new astronomical object.

00:12:15.860 --> 00:12:18.113 position:50% align:center
However, I don't
consider this experience

00:12:18.196 --> 00:12:19.989 position:50% align:center
to have been a waste.

00:12:20.073 --> 00:12:21.658 position:50% align:center
As Hanashima told us,

00:12:21.741 --> 00:12:24.244 position:50% align:center
"This will become precious
information for the others

00:12:24.327 --> 00:12:28.498 position:50% align:center
observing after you."
And I think that's pretty cool.

00:12:28.581 --> 00:12:30.792 position:50% align:center
We'll make use
of these first results.

00:12:30.875 --> 00:12:34.546 position:50% align:center
And then, one day, I'm sure
we'll discover a new object!

00:12:36.089 --> 00:12:38.091 position:50% align:center
[MIRA, TOMORI, MAKITA]
Thank you all very much!

00:12:47.642 --> 00:12:48.935 position:50% align:center
[AO, MIRA giggle]

00:12:51.438 --> 00:12:53.773 position:50% align:center
[AO] Thanks so much for
letting me sit in and watch.

00:12:53.857 --> 00:12:55.108 position:50% align:center
I appreciate it.

00:12:55.191 --> 00:12:57.444 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Yeah, thank you for everything!

00:12:57.527 --> 00:13:00.405 position:50% align:center
So tell me, how was
the Shiny Challenge for you?

00:13:00.488 --> 00:13:02.824 position:50% align:center
Amazing! I'm glad I came.

00:13:02.907 --> 00:13:05.368 position:50% align:center
It's inspired me
to study even more!

00:13:05.452 --> 00:13:08.038 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna discover
an asteroid someday.

00:13:08.121 --> 00:13:10.290 position:50% align:center
This is the start.
What I learned here.

00:13:10.373 --> 00:13:11.708 position:50% align:center
I know it.

00:13:11.791 --> 00:13:13.877 position:50% align:center
I'm really looking
forward to that.

00:13:13.960 --> 00:13:16.004 position:50% align:center
Come back and see us.

00:13:16.087 --> 00:13:18.423 position:50% align:center
--All right!
--Yes!

00:13:18.506 --> 00:13:20.592 position:50% align:center
[MAKITA] If I end up getting
accepted to a university

00:13:20.675 --> 00:13:21.926 position:50% align:center
near you, I'll visit!

00:13:22.010 --> 00:13:23.011 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Okay.

00:13:23.094 --> 00:13:24.596 position:50% align:center
Oh, I want in on this!

00:13:24.679 --> 00:13:27.223 position:50% align:center
I'll come see you guys once I
save enough to come back down!

00:13:27.307 --> 00:13:28.933 position:50% align:center
For Neon's tour!

00:13:29.017 --> 00:13:31.770 position:50% align:center
Hey. Please say I can
stay with you when I do.

00:13:31.853 --> 00:13:33.563 position:50% align:center
Yeah, of course!

00:13:33.646 --> 00:13:35.857 position:50% align:center
[TOMORI] Oh, right!
I want us to take a picture!

00:13:35.940 --> 00:13:38.401 position:50% align:center
[MAKITA] Great idea!
Where should we take it?

00:13:38.485 --> 00:13:40.904 position:50% align:center
Taking a photo? In that case...

00:13:40.987 --> 00:13:42.489 position:50% align:center
There's only one place.

00:13:42.572 --> 00:13:43.740 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU chuckles]

00:13:43.823 --> 00:13:45.075 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS]
Huh...?

00:13:49.037 --> 00:13:50.955 position:50% align:center
I'm ready whenever you are!

00:13:52.540 --> 00:13:54.125 position:50% align:center
One, two...

00:13:57.837 --> 00:13:59.798 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] And that was
the final button on our

00:13:59.881 --> 00:14:02.967 position:50% align:center
Shining Star
Challenge experience.

00:14:04.969 --> 00:14:07.055 position:50% align:center
It went by so fast.

00:14:07.138 --> 00:14:10.308 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Yeah. But I had a lot of fun.

00:14:10.392 --> 00:14:13.645 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] I'm glad we got
to meet Tomorin and Makki.

00:14:13.728 --> 00:14:15.146 position:50% align:center
It was so cool
getting to work with

00:14:15.230 --> 00:14:18.525 position:50% align:center
a whole bunch of people.
From all different fields.

00:14:18.608 --> 00:14:19.901 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:14:19.984 --> 00:14:23.446 position:50% align:center
Y'know, in a way, itt's like
the Earth Science Club.

00:14:23.530 --> 00:14:27.992 position:50% align:center
With both astronomy and geology,
and now, meteorology, too.

00:14:33.456 --> 00:14:35.709 position:50% align:center
[MISA] How did it go
on Ishigaki Island?

00:14:35.792 --> 00:14:38.086 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Awesome! It was so much fun.

00:14:38.169 --> 00:14:40.964 position:50% align:center
[MISA] Oh, good.
That's really great to hear.

00:14:41.047 --> 00:14:43.008 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] I got to hang out
and chat with new friends

00:14:43.091 --> 00:14:45.176 position:50% align:center
under the most
perfect starry sky.

00:14:45.260 --> 00:14:48.221 position:50% align:center
Oh, and we stayed up all night
preparing for the presentation!

00:14:48.304 --> 00:14:50.098 position:50% align:center
Sounds like a great experience.

00:14:50.181 --> 00:14:51.307 position:50% align:center
I'm glad.

00:14:51.391 --> 00:14:52.934 position:50% align:center
[MIRA giggles]

00:14:55.812 --> 00:14:58.064 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] When do you think
you'll be coming home next?

00:15:04.070 --> 00:15:05.238 position:50% align:center
Good to have you back!

00:15:05.321 --> 00:15:06.322 position:50% align:center
Both of you!

00:15:06.406 --> 00:15:08.450 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Yeah, welcome back!

00:15:08.533 --> 00:15:10.118 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Thanks, you guys!

00:15:11.536 --> 00:15:13.329 position:50% align:center
[EVE]
Now, listen, you two.

00:15:13.413 --> 00:15:15.582 position:50% align:center
I'm thinking of running
a special feature.

00:15:15.665 --> 00:15:18.752 position:50% align:center
First issue after break: The
Shining Star Challenge and you.

00:15:18.835 --> 00:15:19.961 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Are you serious?

00:15:20.045 --> 00:15:21.338 position:50% align:center
So, I hope you'll
be willing to give us

00:15:21.421 --> 00:15:23.089 position:50% align:center
an interview soon!

00:15:23.173 --> 00:15:25.342 position:50% align:center
An interview...?

00:15:25.425 --> 00:15:26.801 position:50% align:center
Hey, you guys.

00:15:26.885 --> 00:15:28.428 position:50% align:center
How is everyone doing?

00:15:28.511 --> 00:15:30.180 position:50% align:center
It's Suzu and Megu!

00:15:30.263 --> 00:15:32.390 position:50% align:center
Wow, long time no see!

00:15:32.474 --> 00:15:35.226 position:50% align:center
Right? It really
has been forever!

00:15:35.310 --> 00:15:38.730 position:50% align:center
I brought you some of Suzuya's
delicious breads and sweets.

00:15:38.813 --> 00:15:41.358 position:50% align:center
Oh, man. You already
have a bunch, huh?

00:15:41.441 --> 00:15:43.818 position:50% align:center
[INOSE] They're souvenirs
from Mira and Ao.

00:15:43.902 --> 00:15:45.987 position:50% align:center
Looks like this
is snack-overkill.

00:15:46.071 --> 00:15:48.948 position:50% align:center
Not possible.
We love Suzuya's bread!

00:15:49.032 --> 00:15:51.034 position:50% align:center
I've been dreaming
about it forever!

00:15:51.117 --> 00:15:53.078 position:50% align:center
[SUZU]
I've missed you!

00:15:53.161 --> 00:15:54.496 position:50% align:center
Um, hi.

00:15:54.579 --> 00:15:56.289 position:50% align:center
[MORINO chuckles]

00:15:56.373 --> 00:15:58.875 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Thanks for the snacks!

00:15:58.958 --> 00:16:02.295 position:50% align:center
Big Sis, I need to
head back to my club now.

00:16:02.379 --> 00:16:03.755 position:50% align:center
I'll see ya later.

00:16:03.838 --> 00:16:06.549 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Oh, this is for you, Megu.

00:16:06.633 --> 00:16:07.926 position:50% align:center
Is it star sand?

00:16:08.009 --> 00:16:10.970 position:50% align:center
Look how cute!
Both stars and sand.

00:16:11.054 --> 00:16:12.889 position:50% align:center
Just like the
Earth Sciences Club!

00:16:12.972 --> 00:16:14.391 position:50% align:center
Well, actually.

00:16:14.474 --> 00:16:17.102 position:50% align:center
Those are the shells of a
creature known as Foraminifera!

00:16:17.185 --> 00:16:19.854 position:50% align:center
Yeah. The older ones
are index fossils.

00:16:19.938 --> 00:16:21.940 position:50% align:center
A.K.A, facies fossils.

00:16:22.023 --> 00:16:23.942 position:50% align:center
They're used to determine
the geological period

00:16:24.025 --> 00:16:25.902 position:50% align:center
and the environment of the time.

00:16:25.985 --> 00:16:28.738 position:50% align:center
[SUZU] Megu, it's okay,
you can go on without me.

00:16:28.822 --> 00:16:31.157 position:50% align:center
Okay, thanks again
for the souvenir, guys!

00:16:31.241 --> 00:16:33.618 position:50% align:center
See you all later!

00:16:33.702 --> 00:16:35.954 position:50% align:center
[MORINO]
This is still incredible stuff!

00:16:36.037 --> 00:16:39.124 position:50% align:center
I can't believe you collected
this much in just three days!

00:16:39.207 --> 00:16:42.210 position:50% align:center
[giggles] Yeah, it was
a little challenging.

00:16:42.293 --> 00:16:45.005 position:50% align:center
But we had Ao
helping us out, too!

00:16:45.088 --> 00:16:46.089 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Um.

00:16:46.172 --> 00:16:47.924 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Huh? Y'okay?

00:16:49.009 --> 00:16:50.719 position:50% align:center
Thanks for helping me do this.

00:16:50.802 --> 00:16:52.679 position:50% align:center
I wouldn't have made it
to Ishigaki Island

00:16:52.762 --> 00:16:54.723 position:50% align:center
without you guys.

00:16:54.806 --> 00:16:56.266 position:50% align:center
I'm certain of that.

00:16:56.349 --> 00:16:59.019 position:50% align:center
I never could have
gone on my own.

00:16:59.102 --> 00:17:01.646 position:50% align:center
We wanted you
both to go. Together.

00:17:01.730 --> 00:17:03.356 position:50% align:center
Yeah. Everyone was here,

00:17:03.440 --> 00:17:06.109 position:50% align:center
cheering you on during
our entire summer camp.

00:17:06.192 --> 00:17:07.527 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Mm.

00:17:07.610 --> 00:17:10.530 position:50% align:center
Oh, thanks so much for
the teruteru bouzu dolls, too!

00:17:10.613 --> 00:17:13.491 position:50% align:center
[INOSE] We can't take all the
credit--that was Nana's idea.

00:17:13.575 --> 00:17:17.162 position:50% align:center
Wow, really?
Thank you for that, Nana!

00:17:17.245 --> 00:17:19.414 position:50% align:center
They helped us a lot!

00:17:19.497 --> 00:17:21.833 position:50% align:center
But it's not really a big deal.

00:17:21.916 --> 00:17:24.711 position:50% align:center
Anyway, I've
uploaded the photos.

00:17:24.794 --> 00:17:26.963 position:50% align:center
[INOSE gasps]
I can't wait to see!

00:17:27.047 --> 00:17:28.214 position:50% align:center
[SUZU]
Me, neither!

00:17:30.884 --> 00:17:32.302 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasping]

00:17:33.219 --> 00:17:35.680 position:50% align:center
Oh, gosh! So pretty!

00:17:35.764 --> 00:17:39.392 position:50% align:center
No kidding. I kinda wish
I could've seen it in person!

00:17:39.476 --> 00:17:42.062 position:50% align:center
[CHIKAGE]
Looks like fun.

00:17:42.145 --> 00:17:44.689 position:50% align:center
These two girls
are Tomorin and Makki.

00:17:44.773 --> 00:17:46.358 position:50% align:center
We were in the
same group together.

00:17:46.441 --> 00:17:47.484 position:50% align:center
Tell us more about that!

00:17:47.567 --> 00:17:49.527 position:50% align:center
From the beginning!

00:17:49.611 --> 00:17:52.364 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Oh, it's from Tomorin!

00:17:52.447 --> 00:17:53.531 position:50% align:center
[TOMORI]
Yoo-hoo!

00:17:53.615 --> 00:17:54.908 position:50% align:center
Guess what?

00:17:54.991 --> 00:17:57.243 position:50% align:center
I got to meet Neon in person
at the Star Festival!

00:17:57.327 --> 00:17:59.746 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Wow! Good for you, Tomorin!

00:17:59.829 --> 00:18:02.957 position:50% align:center
[TOMORI] I was so happy,
my memory's missing in places.

00:18:03.041 --> 00:18:04.376 position:50% align:center
[AO]
What?

00:18:04.459 --> 00:18:06.002 position:50% align:center
[MAKITA]
Sounds like temporary amnesia

00:18:06.086 --> 00:18:08.588 position:50% align:center
caused by extreme stress.

00:18:11.800 --> 00:18:13.802 position:50% align:center
[MORINO] Hey. Why don't
we all go stargazing

00:18:13.885 --> 00:18:16.137 position:50% align:center
together since
it's been so long?

00:18:16.221 --> 00:18:18.056 position:50% align:center
I already got
permission for you.

00:18:18.139 --> 00:18:19.140 position:50% align:center
[AO, MIRA]
You did?

00:18:19.224 --> 00:18:21.351 position:50% align:center
How long have
you been standing there?

00:18:21.434 --> 00:18:22.352 position:50% align:center
Here you go.

00:18:22.435 --> 00:18:24.396 position:50% align:center
Thank you! You're the best!

00:18:24.479 --> 00:18:27.691 position:50% align:center
Ah, so she wasn't
just the barbeque pit master.

00:18:27.774 --> 00:18:29.901 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU]
I am your advisor, you know.

00:18:38.743 --> 00:18:41.496 position:50% align:center
We do get a much better
view from the roof, don't we?

00:18:41.579 --> 00:18:43.248 position:50% align:center
Incredible!

00:18:43.331 --> 00:18:46.042 position:50% align:center
I've got it
all lined up! On Jupiter!

00:18:46.126 --> 00:18:48.795 position:50% align:center
Thank you.
You're an expert at that now!

00:18:48.878 --> 00:18:50.255 position:50% align:center
[MIRA giggles]

00:18:50.338 --> 00:18:51.548 position:50% align:center
Can I take a look?

00:18:51.631 --> 00:18:53.883 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Go ahead!

00:18:53.967 --> 00:18:55.301 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI]
It's striped.

00:18:55.385 --> 00:18:59.806 position:50% align:center
[AO] Yeah. And tonight,
you can see four of its moons.

00:18:59.889 --> 00:19:02.058 position:50% align:center
Nana. Could I have a turn next?

00:19:02.142 --> 00:19:03.977 position:50% align:center
Sure.

00:19:04.060 --> 00:19:05.562 position:50% align:center
[CHIKAGE]
It is striped.

00:19:05.645 --> 00:19:07.480 position:50% align:center
[AO chuckles]

00:19:07.564 --> 00:19:09.482 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI]
Hey, Mira. Ao?

00:19:09.566 --> 00:19:12.527 position:50% align:center
--Huh?
--Um... I...

00:19:12.610 --> 00:19:13.862 position:50% align:center
I'm just sorry that this time,

00:19:13.945 --> 00:19:16.322 position:50% align:center
you weren't able to
discover an asteroid.

00:19:16.406 --> 00:19:19.117 position:50% align:center
But, look. Please keep trying!

00:19:19.200 --> 00:19:21.995 position:50% align:center
Hah! Okay! We plan to!

00:19:22.078 --> 00:19:23.496 position:50% align:center
Thanks for that.

00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:29.127 position:50% align:center
Look at that.
Nana's smiling a lot more

00:19:29.210 --> 00:19:30.587 position:50% align:center
than she used to.

00:19:30.670 --> 00:19:31.588 position:50% align:center
What was it like?

00:19:31.671 --> 00:19:33.048 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Now that you mention it...

00:19:33.131 --> 00:19:34.591 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
You're so right!

00:19:34.674 --> 00:19:35.800 position:50% align:center
And Chikage.

00:19:35.884 --> 00:19:38.053 position:50% align:center
She's taken an interest
in astronomy lately.

00:19:38.136 --> 00:19:40.138 position:50% align:center
Oh, has she, really?

00:19:40.221 --> 00:19:42.599 position:50% align:center
That's the same way
it happened for us, too.

00:19:42.682 --> 00:19:45.727 position:50% align:center
Spending so much time around
both Sakurai and Ino.

00:19:45.810 --> 00:19:48.355 position:50% align:center
Our interest in geology
just naturally grew.

00:19:48.438 --> 00:19:49.856 position:50% align:center
Yeah, you're right.

00:19:49.939 --> 00:19:51.900 position:50% align:center
So much has happened!

00:21:36.004 --> 00:21:37.964 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] Everyone has
certain things we love

00:21:38.048 --> 00:21:41.176 position:50% align:center
and certain things
we're good at.

00:21:41.259 --> 00:21:45.263 position:50% align:center
If we isolate ourselves,
that limits our experiences.

00:21:45.347 --> 00:21:47.724 position:50% align:center
But if we connect our
little world to others,

00:21:47.807 --> 00:21:50.602 position:50% align:center
then the possibilities
are endless!

00:21:50.685 --> 00:21:53.730 position:50% align:center
Just like the great unknown.

00:21:53.813 --> 00:21:56.107 position:50% align:center
The cosmos.

00:21:56.191 --> 00:21:57.609 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:22:02.030 --> 00:22:04.908 position:50% align:center
Hey, Ao. Let's discover one.

00:22:04.991 --> 00:22:06.326 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:22:09.329 --> 00:22:11.373 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
We're gonna find it.

00:22:11.456 --> 00:22:13.249 position:50% align:center
[AO]
And it's gonna be amazing.

00:22:14.417 --> 00:22:17.379 position:50% align:center
[AO, MIRA]
We'll fulfill our promise.

00:22:17.462 --> 00:22:18.880 position:50% align:center
Together.